<P>
   COXNET PTECH 0404 _ A high-tech community in Arizona is using a
sophisticated network to bring neighbors together. DC Ranch, with
200 homes occupied and another 6,000 slated for construction, has
made high-speed Internet connections a standard feature of the
houses it sells. Its quiet, cactus-studded streets and upscale
homes are wired with fiber optics and coaxial cable to provide each
household with at least two high-speed, ready-to-surf Internet
connections, six e-mail addresses, and digital TV and telephones _
all for $50 a month. (Holmes, Cox Washington Bureau) Art includes
an attractive 3-column color photo of a man working in his home and
a 1-column color photo of a computer and a big-screen television.
