accordance with Village Ordinance 2791-3 (enacted to keep ugliness
off the streets), I went to the beauty parlor. It was a bust. The
hair came out okay, but it made the rest of me look bad. I keep
telling Karen it must be the lights. I've begged her to ditch the
daylight fluorescents and screw in some of those nice pink bulbs -
the ones that softly shave 10 years off the face in the mirror. She
says if she did that, hair colors in our town would turn freaky -
