<P>
   AUTO-EARNINGS (Detroit) _ General Motors, Ford Motor and
DaimlerChrysler report March sales. By Keith Bradsher.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-TELECOMS (Mexico City) _ A look at the success of
Telefonos de Mexico, the country's dominant telephone company.
Critics contend that Telmex remains an effective monopoly, abetted
by the government, and other potential rivals, including AT&AMP;T and
MCI, are threatening to file a formal complaint with the World
Trade Organization. By Julia Preston.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ Ledeall on the U.S.
government's case against Microsoft: Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson
is expected to issue his ruling on the antitrust case at 5 p.m.
EDT. By Joel Brinkley.
</P>
