_ since it broke ranks with fellow gun makers by agreeing to
introduce a series of safety measures. By JIM HERRON ZAMORA.
</P>
<P>
   SCULPTOR-HEADS (Williamsburg, Va.) _ A sculptor best known for
the huge Sam Houston statue just outside Huntsville, Texas, has
been busy sculpting huge presidential heads and telling everyone
that he has plans for a theme park near Williamsburg, Va. But his
plans aren't going over that well in the cradle of American
history. The local paper has launched a fierce campaign against the
plans, and the heads are sitting atop a flatbed truck in a hotel
parking lot while the sculptor and his investors try to secure the
proper permits. By ALLAN TURNER.
</P>
<P>
   SUBWAY-TABLOID (San Francisco) _ A controversial free tabloid
being distributed on Philadelphia's buses and subways by the local
transit agency may make its next stop at BART _ potentially adding
more twists to the Bay Area's already topsy-turvy newspaper
industry. By MARSHA GINSBURG.
</P>
<P>
   SUNKEN-BOATS (San Francisco) _ The next time your yacht sinks,
call Mitch Marken. ``What I'm good at is finding things,'' said the
veteran undersea explorer. Marken, 39, and his staff divers will
seek the SS Tahoe in Lake Tahoe this summer. By MICHAEL DOUGAN.
</P>
