   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``i'' category)
</P>
<P>
   PERU-TOLEDO (Lima, Peru) _ Despite what many call a dirty-tricks
campaign being waged by President Alberto Fujimori, opposition
candidate Alejandro Toledo could earn enough votes in Peru's April
9 presidential election to force a runoff with Fujimori, analysts
say. Toledo might even win the second round, they add. Toledo, who
rose from poverty to become a Harvard-trained economist, is now No.
2 in the polls. By JOHN OTIS.
</P>
<P>
   PERU-FRAUD (Lima, Peru) _ Electoral observers cite growing fears
that the government will commit fraud in the April 9 elections in
an effort to ensure a first-round victory for President Alberto
Fujimori. By JOHN OTIS.
</P>
