<HEADLINE>
NO THRILLS IN `STAR WARS,' `SIXTH SENSE' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace'' _
Filmmaker George Lucas is releasing this prequel to the ``Star
Wars'' trilogy on VHS, so DVD fans won't get many of the extras
that would make this more an event than just a release. It's worth
saying again: ``Star Wars,'' one of the most successful films of
all time, was such a huge hit because it took everyone by surprise.
``Menace'' fills in the story but not much else.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Sixth Sense'' _ Perhaps in more artistic hands, the
supernatural conceit for this popular movie might work. Unlike
``The Shining,'' which has a series of subtexts, this ghost story
simply rides along on an unconvincing surface. If everyone were as
good as Haley Joel Osment, who's chillingly convincing, it would be
a much better movie. Bruce Willis, given his best role since ``Pulp
Fiction,'' almost pulls it off.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   X MARKS THE SPOT: The entire first season of ``The X-Files,'' on
six DVD discs, will be in stores May 9, the date of this season's
finale and of David Duchovny's exit. An additional disc includes a
documentary on the show, commentary by ``X-Files'' creator Chris
Carter, and assorted other bells and whistles. Priced at $149.98,
it's 20th Century Fox Home Entertainment's first foray into a
definitive boxed set. . . . Krzysztof Kieslowski's ``The
Decalogue'' (1988), 10 hourlong films inspired by the Ten
Commandments, never received major exposure in the United States,
but its international reputation precedes its home-video release on
April 18. (Kieslowski, who died in 1996, is probably best known for
his ``Red/White/Blue'' trilogy.) Available on both VHS and DVD,
each tape contains two episodes, for $19.95. The set is available
for $99.95.
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: April 11: ``The Insider,'' ``Tumbleweeds,''
``Cabaret Balkan,'' ``Thugs,'' ``Three Kings,'' ``Switching
Goals,'' ``Happy, Texas.'' April 18: ``Boys Don't Cry,'' ``Stuart
Little,'' ``Mumford,'' ``House on Haunted Hill,'' ``My Date With
the President's Daughter,'' ``End of Days,'' ``That's the Way I
Like It,'' ``Love Kills.'' April 25: ``Fight Club,'' ``RKO 281,''
``Iris Blond,'' ``Flawless,'' ``Music of the Heart.'' May 2:
``Being John Malkovich,'' ``Galaxy Quest'' (DVD), ``Dogma.'' May 9:
``American Beauty,'' ``Bringing Out the Dead.'' May 16: ``The World
Is Not Enough'' (DVD), ``The End of the Affair.'' May 23: ``Train
of Life.''
</P>
