<P>
   OPEC struck a deal this week to pump a bit more oil on to the
volatile world market. At first blush, such news seems as hard to
criticize as motherhood and apple pie. After all, the volatility of
the past two years has been a curse for all. Yet, it may be a
mistake for Americans to encourage the market manipulators at OPEC.
At best, it will be a Faustian bargain. At worst, America will
needlessly boost the fortunes of a fickle cartel. &QL;
