   &UR; MONTENEGRO CAN BE SAVED FROM MILOSEVIC, IF... &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NEXT-BALKAN-WAR-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Since the end of NATO's war over Kosovo last June, the West's
adversary, Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic, has tightened his
grip on power, at least in his native Serbia, and raised the
rhetorical temperature. Several ominous signs suggest that his next
land grab could be Montenegro, the last remaining republic with
which Serbia is linked in the shrunken Yugoslav federation. &QL;
</P>
