   &UR; SOUTH CAROLINA'S SERIOUS IMAGE PROBLEM &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; `PARIAH'-S.CAROLINA-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A state which used to regard itself as a model of the New South
has once again been ensnared by the politics of the Old South.
South Carolina has had a rough press lately, particularly over the
Confederate flag flying on the dome of its State House. How
embarrassing for a state which prided itself on the peaceful
integration of its schools and public places during the
civil-rights era (unlike neighboring North Carolina, Alabama, and
Mississippi). &QL;
</P>
