   CUBA-ELIAN _ MIAMI _ The Immigration and Naturalization Service
and the Miami family of 6-year-old Cuban rafter Elian Gonzalez meet
again to discuss returning the boy to his father in Cuba. All
indications are, however, that the two sides remain far apart as a
9 a.m. EST Tuesday deadline to terminate Elian's probationary
status in the United States looms. Meanwhile, Cuban President Fidel
Castro says that the visa applications for an entourage led by Juan
Miguel Gonzalez, Elian's father, will be entered today. Developing.
(MWilliams, Cox News Service). 30.
</P>
