<HEADER>
A5777 &Cx1f; taf-z
u e BC-ENTERTAINMENT-NYT-BUD     04-03 0225
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ENTERTAINMENT-NYT-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Entertainment and culture stories from The N.Y. Times News
Service for Tuesday, April 4.
</P>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE-THEATER (Louisville, Ky.) _ A critic's notebook on
the Louisville Theater Festival. By Bruce Weber.
</P>
<P>
   EGYPT-ARCHITECT (New Gourna, Egypt) _ Arts Abroad: Egypt is now
celebrating the 100th anniversary of the birth of its most famous
architect, Hassan Fathy, who received the Aga Khan Award for
Architecture in 1980 in recognition of his influence on post-modern
design but was dismissed as the architect of mud in his own
country. His philosophy was to create cheap housing for the poor
using native materials, indigenous designs and input from the
people who would live in his buildings. By Susan Sachs.
</P>
<P>
   MONDO-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Mondo Desperado,'' by Patrick
McCabe (HarperCollins). Reviewed by Michiko Kakutani.
</P>
<P>
   TV-FALCONE (Undated) _ On CBS, ``Falcone.'' Reviewed by Ron
Wertheimer.
