<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 16:34 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5855 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e BC-FALCONE-PREDECESSORS-     04-03 0290
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FALCONE-PREDECESSORS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ORIGINAL IDEA? FUGEDABOUDIT!
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies TV-FALCONE) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Does the premise for ``Falcone'' sound a little familiar? That's
because it is _ the '80s TV drama ``Wiseguy'' and the 1997 movie
``Donnie Brasco'' played this tune first. So how does ``Falcone''
compare with its predecessors? We take a look ...
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   ``Wiseguy'' (1987-1990)
</P>
<P>
   Story: Obsessive undercover OCB (Organized Crime Bureau) agent
loses self as he doggedly pursues criminal groups. Star: Ken Wahl,
best known for, well, ``Wiseguy.'' (To be fair, he was also in
``Jinxed!'')
</P>
<P>
   Real reason to watch: Guest-star villains like Kevin Spacey,
Jerry Lewis, Ray Sharkey, Fred Thompson, Tim Curry, Debbie Harry,
Stanley Tucci and Glenn Fry. Now playing: In reruns on Court TV.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   ``Donnie Brasco'' (1997)
</P>
<P>
   Story: Obsessive undercover FBI agent loses self as he doggedly
pursues mobsters.
</P>
<P>
   Star: Johnny Depp, best known for romancing Kate Moss and
cutting hedges with his hands.
</P>
<P>
   Real reason to watch: Al Pacino as an embittered, put-upon _ and
ultimately betrayed _ minor-league made-man.
</P>
<P>
   Now playing: At a video store near you.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   ``Falcone'' (2000-)
</P>
<P>
   Story: Obsessive undercover FBI agent loses self as he doggedly
pursues mobsters.
</P>
<P>
   Star: Jason Gedrick, best known for his squeaky-clean image. (He
was Ally McBeal's carwash lover this season.) Real reason to watch:
Airing eight consecutive nights and featuring smirking, witless
characters, it could be confused for ``Who Wants To Be a
Millionaire.''
</P>
<P>
   Now playing: On CBS.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
