<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet PTECH page for the current week. This
layout is available Tuesday after 2 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH 0404 _ A high-tech community in Arizona is using a
sophisticated network to bring neighbors together. DC Ranch, with
200 homes occupied and another 6,000 slated for construction, has
made high-speed Internet connections a standard feature of the
houses it sells. Its quiet, cactus-studded streets and upscale
homes are wired with fiber optics and coaxial cable to provide each
household with at least two high-speed, ready-to-surf Internet
connections, six e-mail addresses, and digital TV and telephones _
all for $50 a month. (Holmes, Cox Washington Bureau) Art includes
an attractive 3-column color photo of a man working in his home and
a 1-column color photo of a computer and a big-screen television.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   GAME CORNER _ As many video games as have been made using the
``Star Wars'' license, you'd think a game that took three years to
develop would blow us out of our collective seats. Unfortunately,
LucasArts' new ``Star Wars'' game, Force Commander isn't it.
(Staff, Austin American-Statesman) Art includes 2-column color
photo from Force Commander.
</P>
<P>
   E-TRAVELER _ Wedding jitters? Ease your marital fears with a
trip to the Web. Here are some wedding-related Web that will have
you walking down the aisle in style. (Staff, Austin
American-Statesman) Art includes a 2-column color illustration of a
car of honeymooners driving away with a computer hanging out of
their car.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY _ The smart way to buy computers is to treat a
computer system like a stereo outfit. Today you might buy a really
good set of speakers, then replace the amplifier in a year or so,
each time getting better stuff. You can do the same thing with
computers. By buying just one component at a time and gradually
replacing the weak links in your system, you can spread out the
cost. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.) Art includes 1 column
color sig of columnist.
</P>
<P>
