<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY _ The smart way to buy computers is to treat a
computer system like a stereo outfit. Today you might buy a really
good set of speakers, then replace the amplifier in a year or so,
each time getting better stuff. You can do the same thing with
computers. By buying just one component at a time and gradually
replacing the weak links in your system, you can spread out the
cost. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.) Art includes 1 column
color sig of columnist.
</P>
