   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-MASTERS-COURSE _ They grew rough. They backed up several tee
boxes as far as they could to create additional length.They've
placed pines where open areas used to be, and they have had, at
times, the speedy greens on the fringe of unplayable. Augusta
National officials have just about used all its options to keep par
reasonable, but as equipment improves, the course continues to seem
shorter and shorter. Rumors persist that the USGA is considering
taking the juice out of golf balls; that might be just what Augusta
needs. Golfers (including Jack Nicklaus) and Augusta officials
discuss the issue. (Bunn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
