Creek this morning on the second leg of a march aimed at convincing
lawmakers to remove the Confederate battle flag from the Statehouse
dome. They were expected to pass a group of flag supporters in
Moncks Corner. (Burritt, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   GINGRICH-DIVORCE _ A lawyer for Newt Gingrich says the former
U.S. House speaker and his wife have signed a final divorce
settlement and are ready to take the agreement to a Cobb County
judge. ``We're all done except for the formality of going to the
judge and getting it approved,'' said attorney Randy Evans. Evans
said the Gingriches will ask Cobb Superior Court Judge Dorothy
Robinson to seal the settlement document. A hearing has not been
set. (Stanford, Cox News Service). 11.
</P>
<P>
   UGA-WRECK _ Pursuing story on a fatal wreck involving five
University of Georgia students late last Thursday. One student died
as a result of injuries from the wreck. The local paper quotes the
Oconee County sheriff as saying officials believe the dead student
was handcuffed and blindfolded in a fraternity hazing incident that
went bad. But the Oconnee Sheriff's Department told the
Jounral-Constitution that the State Patrol is handling the
investigation. The State Patrol said they have released no
information on the wreck other than when it happened, where and how
many people were in car. Everything else is under investigation. No
blood analysis tests have been returned to the State Patrol.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
