<P>
   UNDATED _ Cybill Shepherd made her screen debut in ``The Last
Picture Show,'' playing a sexually active teen-age girl from a
small town. In retrospect, Shepherd was playing herself. Now 50,
she has written an autobiography, ``Cybill Disobedience,'' in which
the movie and TV star recounts her numerous sexual adventures. The
problem is Shepherd manages to make her account boring, detailing
her trysts as if she were reading the ingredients on a box of
cereal. That's too bad because she is known for her biting wit and
outspoken nature, and this could have been more than a thinly
veiled sex book. By DOUGLAS PERRY. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
