away its built-in Internet browser. It could also be obliged to
offer other Windows versions that feature competing browsers.
</P>
<P>
   7. Microsoft is made to change its business practices. One
possibility: It would be barred from striking exclusive licensing
deals or required to publish a price list for its software and
services that would offer all comers the same deal, calling a halt
to current preferences.
