u a BC-NATIONAL-ZOO-PANDA-NY     04-03 0315
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NATIONAL-ZOO-PANDA-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NATIONAL ZOO IS CLOSE TO ACQUIRING 2 PANDAS
</HEADLINE>
   (ms) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The National Zoo, which lost one of its, and
Washington's, biggest attractions last year when its giant panda
died, is nearing an agreement with China that would bring a pair of
pandas here.
</P>
<P>
   Lawrence Small, the head of the Smithsonian Institution, which
runs the zoo, said Monday that the China Wildlife Conservation
Association had expressed a willingness to send the zoo two pandas
under certain conditions.
</P>
<P>
   One, he said, was that the Smithsonian would provide $800,000
annually for the next 10 years for wildlife preservation,
veterinary studies and habitat research in China, or $8 million.
That contribution would be somewhat less than the $10 million that
zoos in San Diego and Atlanta committed for panda pairs they
received from China.
</P>
<P>
   Small said he has raised $5.8 million of the requested $8
million.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are sending a team tomorrow to open discussions,'' Small
said. Many matters remain to be negotiated, he added, including
what would happen if the pair produced offspring and whether the
arrangement could be renewed after 10 years.
</P>
<P>
   He emphasized there was not yet an agreement, but rather ``the
possibility of an agreement.'' A call to the Chinese Embassy was
not immediately returned.
</P>
<P>
   China gave the National Zoo Hsing-Hsing and his mate, Ling-Ling,
in 1972 to mark the revival of American-Chinese relations. The pair
produced five offspring but none lived more than five days.
</P>
<P>
   Ling-Ling died in 1992. Hsing-Hsing was given a lethal injection
Nov. 28 after zookeepers decided that irreversible kidney disease
had made his life too painful.
</P>
<P>
   Hsing-Hsing and Ling-Ling were the favorites of every child, and
their adult minders, who visited the zoo.
</P>
<P>
   ``I deeply want to satisfy those kids,'' Small said.
</P>
</TEXT>
