Snickers candy bar from a convenience store. The man has a previous
conviction for stealing a bag of Oreos plus the theft of tools, so
he was tried as a habitual offender. By KATHY WALT. (Already
filed.)
</P>
<P>
   COLUMBUS-SHIPS (Corpus Christi, Texas) _ Several years ago the
city of Corpus Christi won the much-coveted replicas of Christopher
Columbus' fleet with plans to turn them into a tourist attraction.
Money was raised, facilities were built and tourists visited, but
the project quickly failed. The future is unclear with some wanting
the city to take over and others suggesting the ships go to another
port. By JAMES PINKERTON. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   JUDGES-TEXAS (Austin, Texas) _ A public interest group asks a
federal judge to strike down Texas' money-driven system of electing
judges, contending it unconstitutionally deprives people of neutral
judges. If successful, the lawsuit would force the Texas
Legislature to change the judicial selection system before the 2002
elections. By CLAY ROBISON.
</P>
