A6171 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     04-03 0731
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE MAN WHO CAME TO BREAKFAST
</HEADLINE>
  
 c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   During  &UR; Julia Butterfly Hill &LR; 's two-year stay in the branches of
Luna, a 1,000-year-old redwood tree in Humboldt County, she
entertained several celebrity guests. One of them, she writes in
her new memoir, ``The Legacy of Luna'' (HarperSan Francisco; $25),
was  &UR; Woody Harrelson &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   ``He arrived on a hectic day,'' writes Hill, ``so only later did
we have a chance to really start talking _ about his activism,
about how he got involved, about his family. We stayed up half the
night.''
</P>
<P>
   Harrelson decided to sleep over in the tree. ``I didn't have
that many blankets,'' writes Hill, ``and it was extremely cold and
windy, but I did my best to make him comfortable by giving him half
my covers. Neither of us stayed very warm, but I was more used to
the cold than he was.
</P>
<P>
   ``He had difficulty with the sparse situation, and when the
phone woke us at around six the next morning, he groaned profusely.
He's obviously not a morning person. ...
</P>
<P>
   ```This isn't a five-star hotel,' I said when he jumped on me
about the call. `You're in a tree-sit. This is a campaign. We do
things like deal with the phone at six in the morning. I don't have
a personal assistant to handle things as you do!'''
</P>
<P>
   Harrelson apologized and admitted being ``a little spoiled.''
After his morning ``grumpies'' dissolved, all was well. ``I truly
appreciated the fact that he was real,'' writes Hill, ``even if his
reality was very different from mine.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; LEARNING TO DRESS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Edie Falco &LR;  of ``The Sopranos'' told Allure magazine that she
was both wounded and miffed when  &UR; Melissa Rivers &LR;  named her the
worst-dressed actress at the Emmy awards ceremonies. ``I went to a
conservatory acting program, and now I'm having my feelings hurt by
Melissa Rivers.''
</P>
<P>
   Nonetheless, she accepted the services of an expert hired by HBO
to help her shop for future occasions. ``I had a field day at
DKNY,'' she said, ``and I have a bunch of Armani suits. In a matter
of months, I went from owning Converse high tops to black
 &UR; Manolo Blahnik &LR;  pumps, which, by the way, are stunning.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're breathtaking shoes, like works of art. The language
coming out of my mouth is scaring me, to be honest with you.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. MSNBC says that  &UR; Cate Blanchett &LR;  wanted to keep the dress
she borrowed from  &UR; John Paul Gaultier &LR;  for the Oscars, but the
designer insisted on getting it back. A spokeswoman for Blanchett
said, however, that the actress ``returned it with a nice note of
thanks. How could she ever wear it again? People would say, `Oh,
that's the dress you wore to the Oscars.'''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; Rosie O'Donnell &LR;  is paying for her 20th high school reunion on
Long Island, N.Y., but she has specified that spouses not be
included and that the event be taped to be shown on her talk show.
For those unwilling to play by her rules for the Saturday-night
main event, she's also hosting a breakfast with spouses on Sunday
morning.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
_Wash your ears out with soap: A survey of British surgeons cited
in Self magazine found that orthopedic surgeons were most apt to
curse while operating; ear, nose and throat doctors had the
cleanest speech.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; _ &UR; Frank Zahour  &LR; watched a 1969 episode of ``Dragnet,'' broadcast
on Tuesday, March 28,wherein  &UR; O.J. Simpson  &LR; played a potential
police recruit. He had a line or two, and another sharp-eyed viewer
noted that when Simpson raised his hand to ask a question, he had a
Band-Aid on his finger, just as he did years later in court.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; _ &UR; Cybill Shepherd &LR;  told ``Dateline NBC'' last night that she
wasn't that upset in 1986 when  &UR; Bruce Willis &LR; , her co-star on
``Moonlighting,'' was nominated for an Emmy and she wasn't. ``I was
thinking, `You know, I'll be OK as long as he doesn't win.'''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``The music business just makes me sick. It's just a joke. Can &LR; 
 &UR; you sit and enjoy any kind of music or awards shows? Where are &LR; 
 &UR; the adults? Where is the class? This is whiners and screamers &LR; 
 &UR; and screechers and they're all full of themselves over nothing, &LR; 
 &UR; you know, just like the scum that populates this business. I'm &LR; 
 &UR; ashamed to be a part of it. I hate it with a passion.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Joni Mitchell &LR; , whose new album is ``Both Sides Now,'' in
Rolling Stone.
</P>
