<HEADLINE>
TIMES CO. APPOINTS A VICE PRESIDENT 
</HEADLINE>
  (ms) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Catherine J. Mathis, director of investor relations
at The New York Times Co., has been promoted to vice president for
corporate communications, Michael Golden, the company's vice
chairman, announced Monday. The promotion is effective April 15.
</P>
<P>
   Mathis, 46, who joined the company in 1997, will succeed Nancy
Nielsen, who is leaving to join Harvard University's Center for the
Study of World Religions, where she will develop the strategic plan
for the business segment of its globalization project.
</P>
<P>
   As head of corporate communications, Mathis will oversee
investor relations, media and public relations and crisis
communications and will work with the company's human resources
department on employee communications. She will serve as a
spokeswoman for the company and The New York Times. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
