<P>
   (NYT34) ISRAELI-LEBANESE BORDER, Lebanon -- April 3, 2000 --
ISRAEL-LEBANON -- Israeli soldiers in the ``security zone'' in
southern Lebanon awaited a briefing Monday after their patrol. The
sign reads ``The target: To protect the Northern Border of The
State of Israel.'' Prime Minister Ehud Barak said Monday that he
does not expect a military confrontation after Israeli troops
withdraw from southern Lebanon this summer. But here on the border,
there is anxiety over the consequences for the residents of a
region that has been a proxy battleground for Middle Eastern
adversaries. (Rina Castelnuovo/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT33) NORTH MIAMI BEACH -- April 3, 2000 -- TERM-LIMITS -- For
nearly two decades, Elaine Bloom has been a fixture in the Florida
House of Representatives. Now, at 62, the outspoken Democrat is
running an uphill campaign for Congress against a popular 10-term
Republican incumbent, E. Clay Shaw Jr. This year, politicians like
Ms. Bloom, who are prohibited from running for re-election, are
campaigning instead for higher office against prominent incumbents.
Bloom greeted friends during a recent lunch at a synagogue in North
Miami Beach. (Cindy Karp/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT32) NEW YORK -- April 3, 2000 -- ADROVER-FASHION-3 -- From
