<HEADER>
A6376 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BKN-LAKERS-HARPER-LAD     04-03 0268
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-HARPER-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NO REST FOR HARPER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   EL SEGUNDO -- Ron Harper knew instantly what Kobe Bryant's
Sunday-afternoon brawl meant: No rest for Ron Harper.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Phil Jackson was going to place Harper on the injured list
today, giving him five games to rest his creaky knees for the
playoffs. Rookie John Celestand was to take his place on the
roster.
</P>
<P>
   Although Jackson didn't stick around long enough Monday to
confirm it,Harper said that plan has been scrapped, because Bryant
has been suspended for tonight's game at Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think I'm going to see it,'' Harper, 36, said. ``It's
too close to the end of this year.''
</P>
<P>
   Bryant will be back for Wednesday's game at Golden State, so in
theory, Harper could still get five games off and make it back for
the last two games of the season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I asked (Jackson) about that too,'' Harper said. ``You know
what he told me? He shook his head and said come onto the floor. So
I'm pretty sure I won't be getting any time off.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I told (Bryant) I'm mad at him. I told him I'm not his friend
anymore,'' Harper joked. ``I could use some time off, but since I'm
not going to get any time off, I've got to go out and just have fun
playing.''
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers will start either Derek Fisher or Brian Shaw
alongside Harper tonight. The Lakers are 3-0 against the Suns,
including a victory at Phoenix in November, when Bryant was out
with a broken hand.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm sure other guys will step up,'' said Shaquille O'Neal.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-03-00 2310EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
